source:
{
  "users": [
    {
      "name": "Chris",
      "msgs": 30
    },
    {
      "name": "Emma",
      "msgs": 46
    },
    {
      "name": "Peter",
      "msgs": 10
    },
    {
      "name": "Girl",
      "msgs": 1
    },
    {
      "name": "Nurse",
      "msgs": 5
    }
  ],
  "story": [
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Hey, Chris, do you know about the abandoned mental hospital on the edge of town?",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "No, Emma, don't expect me to go to that asylum",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "You're just a coward!",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Nope!",
      "id": 4
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Okay, sweet couple, stop fighting. Are you coming with me?",
      "id": 5
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Okay",
      "id": 6
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "Okay",
      "id": 7
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "My name is Emma. And yes, I'm a thrill-seeker. My appearance is not important. You'll soon find out why...",
      "id": 8
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "We decided to go there on the weekend. I was glad that my best and only friends had agreed to come with me. Only if I had known what was going to happen there, I would never have gone there with my friends...",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "We agreed to meet at ten o'clock on Saturday morning. We decided to meet at my place",
      "id": 10
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "It's five minutes past ten and they haven't arrived yet",
      "id": 11
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I hear a knock on the door. I look through the peephole and see this \"sweet couple\". I opened the door. They went into the corridor and waited for me to collect all the things",
      "id": 12
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "So, we have a bag of food, and we also have a tent. All right, we can go",
      "id": 13
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "Are we going there in your car or mine?",
      "id": 14
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "I suggest we all go in my car",
      "id": 15
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, and if something happens to you, how am I supposed to go home?",
      "id": 16
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "Then we'll go in your car",
      "id": 17
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Great, that's even better",
      "id": 18
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "We loaded my car with stuff and went to the mental hospital",
      "id": 19
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "What do you know about this place?",
      "id": 20
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "This asylum is a very strange place. Even when it was open, strange things were happening here",
      "id": 21
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "What kind of things?",
      "id": 22
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "What kind of things?",
      "id": 23
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Everyone who was treated here died under mysterious circumstances",
      "id": 24
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "What do you mean? How did they die?",
      "id": 25
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "No one knows. It's a well-kept secret",
      "id": 26
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "When will we get there?",
      "id": 27
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "We've already arrived",
      "id": 28
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I turned off the car and got out",
      "id": 29
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Even the air here is different",
      "id": 30
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "I want to go home...",
      "id": 31
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "Let's go already!",
      "id": 32
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Chris and I walked toward the asylum",
      "id": 33
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I overtook Peter and was ahead of everyone",
      "id": 34
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "The three of us stood at the door to the mysterious building. I took the wire cutters out of my bag and cut the chain",
      "id": 35
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Let's go!",
      "id": 36
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "I don't feel comfortable. Can we go home?",
      "id": 37
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "What are you talking about, Chris? We've just arrived here!",
      "id": 38
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "It just seems to me that there is something or someone here",
      "id": 39
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "To be honest, I don't feel comfortable either",
      "id": 40
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Come on! What's wrong with you?",
      "id": 41
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "This place is creeping me out. Let's go home",
      "id": 42
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Okay, let's just go to the director's office",
      "id": 43
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "What for?",
      "id": 44
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Well, we have to! Stop whining! Let's go!",
      "id": 45
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I took them by the hand and led them inside the asylum. I know approximately where it is",
      "id": 46
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Turn left now! Oh, My God! What's this?",
      "id": 47
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I stared at the wall in horror. There was a man hanging on it... A gutted man... As I stared at the body, Chris threw up. When I turned to her, I heard something fall. When I turned back to the hanging body, the guts fell out of it. I stifled the urge to vomit",
      "id": 48
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Guys, let's go find this damn office and get out of here!",
      "id": 49
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "My friends agreed with me, and we rushed to find the office",
      "id": 50
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "After an hour of searching, we found it... I ran in, swept all the papers into my bag, and ran out of the office",
      "id": 51
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Guys, hurry up, or I'm going to die of fright",
      "id": 52
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I didn't say anything, just ran toward the exit. Peter picked up Chris and ran after me. It took us five minutes to reach my car. I tossed my bag in the trunk and got behind the wheel. I started the car and stepped on the gas",
      "id": 53
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "In 10 minutes we were driving along the сentral road",
      "id": 54
    },
    {
      "user": 2,
      "text": "Chris, are you okay?",
      "id": 55
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "I think I'll survive",
      "id": 56
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Peter hugged Chris",
      "id": 57
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Sweet couple...",
      "id": 58
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "And she smiled)",
      "id": 59
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Don't spoil the moment, Emma",
      "id": 60
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I didn't say anything",
      "id": 61
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "When I pulled up to Peter's house, I looked at the backseat. Chris was sleeping with Peter in his arms. Peter wasn't asleep",
      "id": 62
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I opened the car door, Peter picked up Chris and went home with her. I watched them go. When they were out of sight, I got in my car and drove home",
      "id": 63
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I went into my house and read the papers I had taken from the director's office at the mental hospital",
      "id": 64
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "The first file folder I came across was called \"Mike Crums\"",
      "id": 65
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I picked up the folder and opened it. A photo fell out of the folder. I picked it up and looked at it. I couldn't believe my eyes. Is this Peter's brother? I found his file in the folder. It was definitely Peter's brother. He suffered from autism and fits of anger. What a poor thing! He was in the mental hospital for less than six months, then committed suicide. He choked on a wisp of his own hair... What was going on in this hospital? I put this folder aside and picked up another. It says: \"Linda Kraus\". I read her file and was appalled. She chewed through her roommate's stomach and hung herself with her intestines. That's horrible. I put that folder aside, too",
      "id": 66
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I noticed on some book the inscription \"Dia\". I opened it and read the full title. It was called \"Diary\". The author's name was not given. And if you look closely, it doesn't look like a book. Most likely, this is a personal diary",
      "id": 67
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I opened the first page and read about the owner of this diary. His name was John Grace. It's a strange name. He was the director of this asylum. He worked here, according to the last record, for about two years. I turned the pages to the beginning of the notes and began to read",
      "id": 68
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "November 18, 2011",
      "id": 69
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I finally finished building this mental hospital. I hope I will be able to help people",
      "id": 70
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "November 30, 2011",
      "id": 71
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I put an ad in the newspaper and got a call two days later. Then I put up some ads around the town, and soon I got a call from 8 more people",
      "id": 72
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "December 1, 2011",
      "id": 73
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I've set up an interview for tomorrow. I hope I can recruit staff for the hospital",
      "id": 74
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "December 3, 2011",
      "id": 75
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I recruited staff at the hospital",
      "id": 76
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "December 31, 2011",
      "id": 77
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I and my employees decided to celebrate the New year together. My hospital is in demand among people",
      "id": 78
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "February 4, 2012",
      "id": 79
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Something is happening here. Patients commit suicide... Tomorrow I will invite a priest to the hospital to consecrate it",
      "id": 80
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "February 5, 2012",
      "id": 81
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "He's disappeared",
      "id": 82
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "The priest is missing...",
      "id": 83
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "He finished consecrating the right wing of the hospital and went to the left wing. And he didn't come back... I'm scared... The staff of the right wing doesn't yet know what is happening in the left wing, since only the best specialists work there. What's going on here?",
      "id": 84
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "March 1, 2012",
      "id": 85
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I invited another priest. Everything went well. Only one of the patients was acting strangely...",
      "id": 86
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "August 30, 2012",
      "id": 87
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "It all started again... Now not only patients but also staff are behaving strangely... Is this place cursed?",
      "id": 88
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "October 8, 2012",
      "id": 89
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Yesterday I went to the church and bought some icons. Today I again invited the priest to the hospital and once again asked him to consecrate it",
      "id": 90
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "",
      "id": 91
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "October 9, 2012",
      "id": 92
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I hired some workers to make shelves for icons in every room",
      "id": 93
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "November 1, 2012",
      "id": 94
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Everything was fine after the icons were hung in the hospital. Thank God!",
      "id": 95
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "November 4, 2013",
      "id": 96
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "No, no, no! It's all happening again! Only yesterday 8 people died! 5 of them were my medical workers! I don't know what to do!",
      "id": 97
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "November 15, 2013",
      "id": 98
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I'm starting to hear voices. They are terrible... They say that bare wires are delicious... Maybe they're right?\"",
      "id": 99
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "At this point, the notes in the diary end. Was he dead, too? I need to look up information about this mental hospital on the Internet",
      "id": 100
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I looked at my watch. It's midnight. I got up and went to the window. There's a full moon today. It's just like in a horror movie. And now someone has to ring the doorbell. The doorbell rang. Now I'm scared. Who needs me at this hour of the night?",
      "id": 101
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I plucked up the courage to go to the door. I looked through the peephole and saw Chris. That's a relief. I opened the door and she came in",
      "id": 102
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "I'm so glad it's you!",
      "id": 103
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "What do you mean?",
      "id": 104
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "In short, I looked at my watch, it was midnight. Then I went to the window, and there was a full moon outside. And I'm like, \"Just like in a horror movie. And now, someone has to ring the doorbell\". And then you ring the doorbell. I was so scared. But I opened the door, and there you are, what a relief!",
      "id": 105
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "I see...",
      "id": 106
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Is something wrong?",
      "id": 107
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Yes... Peter is dead",
      "id": 108
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "W-what? H-how?",
      "id": 109
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Well. I woke up hearing screams. I-I ran to help, but it was too late. Something was eating him. I-I ran out of the apa-apartment and ran to y-you. I-I don't know what to do",
      "id": 110
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "She began to cry. I hugged her",
      "id": 111
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Peter can't be brought back to life. Calm down. We will definitely find a way out of this situation. Do you remember what that creature looked like?",
      "id": 112
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Y-yeah. I r-remember",
      "id": 113
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Can you draw it?",
      "id": 114
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "I c-can",
      "id": 115
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Okay",
      "id": 116
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I went to get a piece of paper and a pencil. Chris had calmed down a little. I gave her the paper and then went to the kitchen for a sedative, taking her drawing. At first I thought this drawing was copied from somewhere, but then I realized that Chris wouldn't lie to me. She doesn't have that habit. An eyeless creature with a huge mouth stared at me from the drawing. I was afraid of the drawing, and Chris saw this monster live. This is terrible!",
      "id": 117
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Emma, can I stay with you? I'm afraid to go home now",
      "id": 118
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "You don't even need to ask. Of course you can. I'm afraid to let you go myself. So go sleep in my room",
      "id": 119
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "What about you?",
      "id": 120
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "What about me? I'll lie on the floor in my room",
      "id": 121
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Why on the floor?",
      "id": 122
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "I'm afraid to sleep alone now",
      "id": 123
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "I see",
      "id": 124
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "15 minutes later, Chris was asleep. I was playing games on my laptop. I didn't feel like sleeping at all. And everything should be fine, but no! My cat wanted to eat! I reluctantly got up and went to the kitchen to give my favorite cat something to eat. I gave him dry food and poured myself a cup of tea. It would have been all right, but as I passed the door, I heard a soft knock on it. I thought I was imagining it, and was about to go to my room when the knock came again. I went to the door and looked through the peephole. The cup of tea fell from my hands. Behind the door was the creature that had eaten Peter. I quickly moved away from the door and ran to my room. In the room, I quickly turned off my laptop and started to wake Chris",
      "id": 125
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Chris, get up! It's here!",
      "id": 126
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "What do you mean?",
      "id": 127
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "The creature that ate Peter! It's here!",
      "id": 128
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "What?",
      "id": 129
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Yeah. We have to do something",
      "id": 130
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "But what exactly should we do? Wait, do you hear that?",
      "id": 131
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I stopped talking and listened. Someone came out of the next apartment and it seemed to notice him. Then we heard cries for help. I held Chris's hands. After all, she might not be lucky a second time",
      "id": 132
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Chris and I sat in my room until morning, and the knocking on the door didn't stop. During this time, I tried to understand why this monster came for us. Maybe it's due to the fact that we visited the mental hospital? No, there must be another reason",
      "id": 133
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Hey, Chris, did you and Peter summon any spirits?",
      "id": 134
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "How do you know?",
      "id": 135
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Well, I guessed",
      "id": 136
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I didn't say anything else. Chris was silent too",
      "id": 137
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "The sun rose and the knocking stopped",
      "id": 138
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I went to the front door and opened it. The creature was not there. There were only the corpses of my neighbors. I don't know why, but I don't feel sorry for them. I hated them anyway. I can't even explain the reason for my hatred. Chris followed me out of the apartment",
      "id": 139
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "I th-think I'll go home",
      "id": 140
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "All right. Call me when you get there",
      "id": 141
    },
    {
      "user": 0,
      "text": "Ok",
      "id": 142
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I waved at her and went home. At home, I immediately ran to my laptop. I sat down at the table and put on my headphones and started searching for information about this mental hospital",
      "id": 143
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Two hours later, Chris still hadn't called. She always keeps her word. Maybe she went somewhere? It's possible",
      "id": 144
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "It turns out that before the asylum there used to be a church where the exorcism was performed. Now I understand why strange things happened there. Hmm, wait a minute. Since I was there, does that mean I'm possessed now, too? Although, according to notes in John Grace's diary, it took him about two years to become possessed. It's so confusing",
      "id": 145
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "It's been four hours since Chris left. I'm starting to worry. I call her, and she doesn't pick up the phone. I don't like that",
      "id": 146
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "It's almost three o'clock in the afternoon, and I haven't eaten yet. I got dressed and put on my sneakers. I took my keys, closed the door, and headed for the stairs. I lived on the third floor. When I got down to the second floor, I saw someone's foot. I didn't think much of it at first. There are a lot of drunks in the apartment building, but my curiosity got the better of me. I went to the body and screamed. It was Chris... I fell on my knees and started crying. I couldn't stop crying. Tears were pouring from my eyes. My last friend died... I could have accepted Peter's death, but not Chris's. We were friends for eleven years. She was so dear to me...",
      "id": 147
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Suddenly, I heard a voice. It came from my floor... I went up the stairs and saw IT. I immediately ran out of the entrance of the building and ran to the park",
      "id": 148
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Oh, My God! What's going on here?",
      "id": 149
    },
    {
      "user": 3,
      "text": "Hey, girl, what's wrong with you?",
      "id": 150
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Nothing! Everything is great! My friends were killed by some infernal monster, and now it's in my house! Oh, come on. It's okay!",
      "id": 151
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I yelled at the woman. She took a step back and ran away. I fell to my knees and laughed... I was laughing like a complete psychopath... It must have looked awful...",
      "id": 152
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "After sitting there for another five minutes, I got up and walked toward my house. I didn't care if the monster was still there.",
      "id": 153
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I entered the apartment building and went up to my floor. As I walked up the stairs, I didn't see Chris's body. There were no bodies at all. Only blood was everywhere. I barely made it to my door, afraid I might fall. I opened the door and went inside. I took those papers and went downstairs. When I came out of the house, I threw my lighter in there. I hope this house burns down. I got in my car and went to that mental hospital",
      "id": 154
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I was there in half an hour. I didn't stop at the gate, I tore it down with my car and drove into the yard of the asylum",
      "id": 155
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Well, I'm here!",
      "id": 156
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Kicking the door open, I went to find someone",
      "id": 157
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Hey! Have you all gone into hiding? You are cowards! Come out and show yourself!",
      "id": 158
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I screamed into the void and laughed wildly. I knew I didn't have long to live, but I wanted to die with a smile",
      "id": 159
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I started running all over the building",
      "id": 160
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Suddenly, I heard the sound of a hammer hitting something metal",
      "id": 161
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Finally! I didn't expect that I wouldn't have to wait long",
      "id": 162
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I ran towards the sound, I didn't understand why I was doing this... I ran to this creature as if it were a cute kitten... I've lost my mind...",
      "id": 163
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "Just before I turned the corner, the sound stopped... I felt a little hurt...",
      "id": 164
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I heard a siren outside. The police? But from where? I have nothing to lose. I came out with my hands up and a crazy smile on my face. Two women ran up to me. They were paramedics. They put me in the car. As it turned out later, I was taken to the hospital. But why?",
      "id": 165
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "They drove for about fifteen minutes. For ten minutes I thought about my failures in life. Yeah. What a time it was then",
      "id": 166
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "As I sat there laughing, the paramedic injected some medicine into my shoulder and I fell asleep. I woke up in a hospital room. I wanted to scratch my leg, but my hands were tied. Well, actually, they were not tied. I was in a straitjacket. If I'm in a straitjacket, I'm in a mental hospital. What a great news!",
      "id": 167
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "The nurse came to me and brought something on a tray. It was a bowl of semolina. I hate semolina",
      "id": 168
    },
    {
      "user": 4,
      "text": "Oh, you're awake already! I brought you breakfast",
      "id": 169
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Untie me, please, I'm in pain",
      "id": 170
    },
    {
      "user": 4,
      "text": "But I can't...",
      "id": 171
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "I beg you!",
      "id": 172
    },
    {
      "user": 4,
      "text": "But I can't untie you...",
      "id": 173
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Please, I'm begging you!!!",
      "id": 174
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "And I made puppy eyes",
      "id": 175
    },
    {
      "user": 4,
      "text": "Just for a little while...",
      "id": 176
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Oh, thank you",
      "id": 177
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "She took that awful straitjacket off of me. I stretched. My bones crunched!",
      "id": 178
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "She gave me a bowl of semolina. I looked at semolina with disdain",
      "id": 179
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Well, hello, my worst enemy",
      "id": 180
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I said this looking at the bowl",
      "id": 181
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "The nurse gave me a spoon. I went to the door and closed it. The nurse looked at me in horror. I went to her and pushed her to the floor. She fell. I sat on her legs",
      "id": 182
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "You're so naive. Maybe you should die?",
      "id": 183
    },
    {
      "user": 4,
      "text": "Oh, please... Don't kill me!",
      "id": 184
    },
    {
      "user": 1,
      "text": "Go mad with pain and despair!",
      "id": 185
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "After that, I shoved the spoon down her throat. She moved so comically when she was out of breath. I had a good laugh, so to speak. I waited until she stopped twitching and poured the semolina over her face. This is perfect. I defeated two of my enemies. I feel like a superhero. I let out a wild laugh",
      "id": 186
    },
    {
      "user": -1,
      "text": "I jumped up and started to take deep breaths. It's just a dream. Just a terrible dream. I sat on the bed and thought about every detail of the dream. Suddenly there was a scratching at the door...",
      "id": 187
    }
  ],
  "msgIndex": 187
}
